WEBVTT

00:40.457 --> 00:43.376
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES, GROUPS, AND
ORGANIZATIONS IN THIS WORK ARE FICTITIOUS

00:43.460 --> 00:46.379
SCENES WITH ANIMALS ARE STAGED
ACCORDING TO ANIMAL WELFARE GUIDELINES

01:07.650 --> 01:11.529
This place used to be
a popular billiard club in this town.

01:13.073 --> 01:14.574
It's really spacious, isn't it?

01:19.079 --> 01:21.039
You'll never guess how much the rent is.

01:22.582 --> 01:24.167
It's only 50,000 won!

01:25.210 --> 01:26.461
Isn't that shocking?

01:29.464 --> 01:32.592
Plus, I get to use
this whole building by myself.

01:33.092 --> 01:35.470
I'm practically the owner of the building.

01:41.434 --> 01:45.396
To be frank, I'm worried about being alone
but I'm also excited.

01:46.940 --> 01:49.025
I wonder what will happen from now on.

01:59.035 --> 02:03.081
I calculated how much
I have saved up until now.

02:03.581 --> 02:04.791
Goodness.

02:04.874 --> 02:07.919
This is all Mom's money
except for 500,000 won.

02:08.002 --> 02:08.837
5.5 MILLION

02:08.920 --> 02:12.132
I only have 500,000 won
after working for four years.

02:12.841 --> 02:14.592
Where did all my money go?

02:20.765 --> 02:23.810
That's why I try to eat at home.

02:23.893 --> 02:24.769
It's hot.

02:24.853 --> 02:27.647
Sir, do you have a lantern here
by any chance?

02:27.730 --> 02:28.857
It's 10,000 won.

02:28.940 --> 02:31.860
-I only buy what's necessary.
-This is soft.

02:31.943 --> 02:32.986
If I buy this too,

02:33.069 --> 02:35.029
-can I get a discount?
-A discount?

02:35.113 --> 02:36.906
It's always quantity over quality.

02:36.990 --> 02:39.159
-Yes, this is cornbread.
-One of those, please.

02:39.242 --> 02:43.580
Living here, I've decided
to only use 10,000 won a day.

02:44.289 --> 02:47.792
That's the only way I can get by
for a year without working.

02:47.876 --> 02:49.460
You may ask, "isn't it tough?"

02:49.544 --> 02:51.921
No, completely the opposite.

03:04.309 --> 03:06.269
I have my own hideout.

03:09.063 --> 03:12.358
Although I did make
a commotion here at first.

03:12.942 --> 03:16.154
I can read all day here

03:17.488 --> 03:20.408
and watch all the movies I want.

03:25.622 --> 03:27.540
I can rest and enjoy nature at leisure

03:29.000 --> 03:30.752
and walk about wherever I please.

03:31.544 --> 03:33.630
I even took up jogging in the morning.

03:34.422 --> 03:36.507
Because time is all I have.

03:53.775 --> 03:55.026
Mom.

03:56.069 --> 03:58.238
This is how I'm living.

04:00.531 --> 04:02.659
Are you doing well up there?

04:04.202 --> 04:05.495
I miss you.

04:06.120 --> 04:07.121
A lot.

04:24.514 --> 04:26.599
Look at her.

04:26.683 --> 04:27.934
Gosh.

04:28.810 --> 04:30.895
-My goodness.
-Hello.

04:30.979 --> 04:33.481
Do you have AAA batteries here?

04:33.564 --> 04:36.150
Jeong-hun must have caused trouble again.

04:36.818 --> 04:39.404
-What did you need?
-AAA batteries.

04:40.446 --> 04:43.491
They are over there.
Which one are you looking for?

04:43.574 --> 04:45.118
I'll go take a look.

04:46.786 --> 04:48.955
Why does he love drinking so much?

04:49.038 --> 04:51.582
It'll be the death of him.

04:51.666 --> 04:53.126
Let's go home.

04:53.209 --> 04:55.378
-Darn it.
-Stand up.

04:55.461 --> 04:56.963
Get a hold of yourself.

04:57.046 --> 04:59.132
Move, damn it!

04:59.841 --> 05:01.551
-Damn.
-Goodness.

05:03.469 --> 05:05.555
-Are you okay?
-Yes, I'm okay.

05:05.638 --> 05:07.390
I'm fine. Thank you.

05:07.473 --> 05:09.684
-Hey, stand up.
-Don't touch me.

05:09.767 --> 05:12.353
-Let's go home.
-I don't want to.

05:12.437 --> 05:14.105
Please stand up.

05:14.188 --> 05:16.024
-Mister, please get up.
-What the hell?

05:16.107 --> 05:17.567
-Get up.
-Hold on.

05:17.650 --> 05:19.068
Mister.

05:19.152 --> 05:20.987
-I can't walk.
-Get it together.

05:21.738 --> 05:24.365
My mom is such a pitiful woman.

05:24.449 --> 05:25.450
Let's go home.

05:25.533 --> 05:28.286
-Where's your home?
-It's a bit far.

05:28.369 --> 05:30.872
-I'll help you take him home.
-Thank you.

05:31.456 --> 05:34.459
Jeong-hun,
wake up and try to walk properly.

05:36.127 --> 05:38.421
-Let's put him over there.
-Okay.

05:39.130 --> 05:40.214
Goodness.

05:45.261 --> 05:47.847
Gosh. You're exhausted, right?

05:48.431 --> 05:50.016
Thank you so much.

05:50.099 --> 05:52.101
I managed to bring him home thanks to you.

05:52.185 --> 05:53.728
I'll get going then.

05:53.811 --> 05:55.813
Hold on. Just a moment.

06:00.234 --> 06:02.278
-Here.
-Thank you.

06:02.904 --> 06:05.573
-Thank you so much.
-It's nothing.

06:05.656 --> 06:08.743
Make sure you apply ointment
on your hands.

06:08.826 --> 06:11.579
-Of course.
-Damn it. Hey.

06:11.662 --> 06:14.123
-I'll be going.
-Goodbye.

06:14.665 --> 06:16.542
You fucking bitch!

06:16.626 --> 06:18.586
-Goodness, Jeong-hun!
-Fuck!

06:18.669 --> 06:21.506
We're home now. Get yourself together now.

06:39.357 --> 06:41.692
Liquor must be a real problem.

06:46.030 --> 06:47.198
No, it's not.

06:47.907 --> 06:49.742
People are the real problem.

06:51.327 --> 06:52.537
-Come on!
-Gosh!

06:53.037 --> 06:55.081
-Shoot her!
-Go away!

06:55.164 --> 06:57.416
-Get out of her!
-Shoot!

06:57.500 --> 06:58.459
Stop it!

06:58.543 --> 06:59.877
How did you come in here?

06:59.961 --> 07:01.170
What about you, old lady?

07:01.254 --> 07:02.839
This is our building.

07:02.922 --> 07:04.882
Hey, this is my house. Get out!

07:04.966 --> 07:06.008
You live here?

07:06.092 --> 07:07.593
Are you homeless, old lady?

07:07.677 --> 07:09.846
How could a billiard club be your house?

07:10.513 --> 07:12.223
-It's a house, let's leave now.
-Shoot!

07:12.306 --> 07:14.183
-Get out!
-Shoot her!

07:14.267 --> 07:16.477
-Shoot!
-Do you want a piece of me?

07:17.562 --> 07:19.313
-No!
-Run!

07:19.397 --> 07:22.108
-Run away!
-Quick!

07:22.191 --> 07:23.776
-Let's go.
-Go.

07:30.324 --> 07:31.826
Those little brats.

07:34.579 --> 07:35.705
What's up with this?

07:49.886 --> 07:51.637
What do I do?

07:51.721 --> 07:53.347
What's wrong with this thing?

08:09.155 --> 08:11.449
ANGOK SUPERMARKET

08:16.496 --> 08:19.499
Gosh, to what do I owe the pleasure?

08:19.582 --> 08:21.083
Yes, hello.

08:21.167 --> 08:23.044
The water pipe is leaking.

08:23.127 --> 08:25.046
I see. The water pipe.

08:25.671 --> 08:28.591
Goodness, it must be a mess over there.

08:28.674 --> 08:30.176
Yes, so I was wondering…

08:30.259 --> 08:33.930
Come on, I hope you're not calling me
to ask me to fix the pipe.

08:34.472 --> 08:35.973
We had an agreement.

08:36.057 --> 08:39.101
I thought I told you
to take care of it yourself.

08:39.685 --> 08:43.564
But you know, the windows don't close
and the doors don't shut properly there.

08:43.648 --> 08:45.566
There are loads of things
that need fixing.

08:46.275 --> 08:51.030
Then could you at least give me a number
for a handyman to contact?

08:51.113 --> 08:52.907
Right, a handyman?

08:52.990 --> 08:54.075
A handyman.

08:54.575 --> 08:56.077
I haven't thought of that.

08:56.160 --> 08:58.996
-Mister!
-But the amount he charges for the service

08:59.080 --> 09:01.290
-Mister.
-is more than your rent for six months.

09:01.374 --> 09:04.043
-Come on!
-Do you still…

09:04.126 --> 09:05.836
-Come on!
-Hello?

09:05.920 --> 09:06.963
-Give us the money!
-What did you say?

09:07.046 --> 09:08.923
So the price is… Excuse me.

09:09.006 --> 09:10.424
Be quiet, you brats!

09:10.508 --> 09:13.010
-Who are you on a call with?
-Give us the money!

09:13.094 --> 09:14.095
Lady, just leave.

09:14.178 --> 09:17.515
I'll talk to my dad
and ask him to give you back the money.

09:17.598 --> 09:20.685
It's fine. I'll just fix it up myself.

09:20.768 --> 09:22.103
-Come on!
-Hang up!

09:23.396 --> 09:24.605
Gosh, this lady.

09:24.689 --> 09:26.107
You little brats.

09:26.190 --> 09:28.109
Couldn't you see I was on a call?

09:28.192 --> 09:29.527
Why were you being so noisy?

09:29.610 --> 09:31.779
-Give me the money first.
-Give us some money.

09:31.862 --> 09:33.531
-There you go.
-Seriously.

09:33.614 --> 09:35.783
You and your grandpa
steal so much money away.

09:35.866 --> 09:37.493
Here you go.

09:38.911 --> 09:40.663
Is that all?

09:41.289 --> 09:43.124
-Gosh!
-Give us at least 10,000 won!

09:43.207 --> 09:45.835
-You didn't do your jobs properly!
-What are you saying?

09:45.918 --> 09:49.380
You said you would give us 10,000 won
for causing trouble with the water!

09:49.463 --> 09:52.508
It was tough for us to act excited!

09:52.592 --> 09:54.552
Fine. Have it your way.

09:54.635 --> 09:55.803
Here.

09:55.886 --> 09:57.263
Then give that money back.

09:57.847 --> 09:59.599
-Thanks, Dad.
-Let's go!

09:59.682 --> 10:02.059
-Bye!
-Goodbye!

10:02.143 --> 10:04.770
Don't use it all at once! Save it up!

10:34.091 --> 10:36.093
I'll just be careful with it.

10:51.484 --> 10:53.653
I heard that lady comes here often.

10:56.238 --> 10:57.573
Are you interested in her?

10:57.657 --> 11:00.534
What are you saying?
Listen carefully, Bom.

11:00.618 --> 11:02.244
I hate…

11:03.954 --> 11:06.082
tanned and skinny girls like her.

11:06.165 --> 11:09.585
-I like girls who--
-She hates you too. Wake up.

11:10.670 --> 11:11.754
Gosh.

11:12.296 --> 11:16.133
I heard she came into the library drunk
and fell asleep there.

11:16.717 --> 11:19.887
Gosh, this town literally has no secrets.

11:19.970 --> 11:23.724
Her behavior shows
she has no respect for the countryside.

11:23.808 --> 11:26.143
She buttered up my old man
to rent the billiard club

11:26.227 --> 11:28.104
for 50,000 won a month.

11:28.187 --> 11:30.314
Isn't that ridiculous?

11:30.398 --> 11:31.649
So what?

11:32.441 --> 11:35.444
Why did you call me?
Was it so we could gossip about her?

11:36.028 --> 11:37.071
Gosh.

11:37.154 --> 11:38.656
-I'm leaving.
-Hey, wait.

11:39.532 --> 11:41.492
Do you want a part-time job?

11:42.410 --> 11:43.619
What part-time job?

11:43.702 --> 11:44.829
I'll pay you 50,000 won.

11:46.288 --> 11:47.498
What? 50,000 won?

11:50.167 --> 11:51.210
Start talking.

11:51.293 --> 11:52.586
NON-POSSESSION BY BEOPJEONG

12:11.814 --> 12:13.399
Let's not avoid him.

12:13.983 --> 12:15.693
I'll be seeing him every day anyway.

12:19.155 --> 12:20.448
Do you…

12:20.531 --> 12:22.408
repair all the books yourself?

12:22.491 --> 12:23.784
Yes.

12:32.710 --> 12:34.378
Can I try too?

12:35.546 --> 12:36.589
Sorry?

12:38.215 --> 12:39.800
You take the spatula

12:40.634 --> 12:43.262
and spread the glue evenly,

12:43.345 --> 12:47.266
and you place the page
at its original location.

12:51.854 --> 12:53.022
And then…

12:56.859 --> 12:58.194
And that's it.

12:59.987 --> 13:02.865
You're like a doctor.

13:02.948 --> 13:05.117
It's like you're applying
medicine to the books.

13:06.619 --> 13:07.703
I think…

13:09.330 --> 13:10.581
I'm in love.

13:14.418 --> 13:15.794
What I mean is…

13:16.378 --> 13:20.716
I think I'm in love with the process

13:20.799 --> 13:23.552
of fixing up old things.

13:24.595 --> 13:25.679
I see.

13:27.515 --> 13:29.391
Let me help you.

13:39.568 --> 13:44.865
Has anyone told you
that you're like Santiago?

13:45.783 --> 13:47.785
-Me?
-Yes.

13:48.911 --> 13:52.289
The old man from The Old Man and the Sea.

13:52.373 --> 13:54.708
-You know him, right?
-I do.

13:55.626 --> 13:57.920
When I first met you,

13:58.504 --> 14:01.006
that character came to my mind.

14:08.305 --> 14:09.682
Which one was this?

14:09.765 --> 14:10.933
What do I do?

14:26.657 --> 14:28.784
Did you memorize all of these?

14:28.868 --> 14:30.035
No.

14:31.370 --> 14:35.207
I only remember the names
and the places in the books.

14:35.291 --> 14:39.044
I can never memorize the names
even after I read them multiple times.

14:41.088 --> 14:43.632
Why don't you try this one, Ms. Lee?

14:45.634 --> 14:47.011
I'll give it a try.

14:52.308 --> 14:53.851
Are you helping us out?

14:53.934 --> 14:55.603
-Hello.
-Hello.

14:55.686 --> 14:57.646
Well, actually…

14:58.397 --> 15:00.274
I'm not sure if I'm helping at all.

15:03.611 --> 15:06.030
-It's not even summer, but there's a fly.
-I know.

15:06.113 --> 15:08.407
How come you're having lunch so late?

15:13.787 --> 15:16.415
Don't even think about it. Just get out.

15:18.667 --> 15:20.669
Look here.

15:21.253 --> 15:25.299
Do you think I came all the way here
without a plan?

15:26.550 --> 15:27.718
-Attitude.
-Gosh.

15:27.801 --> 15:29.136
What's gotten into you?

15:29.219 --> 15:30.888
Your attitude.

15:30.971 --> 15:32.556
What are you talking about?

15:34.141 --> 15:35.267
Listen.

15:36.101 --> 15:38.729
When city folks move to the countryside,

15:39.271 --> 15:41.857
do you know why they come here excited
but leave in tears?

15:41.941 --> 15:43.067
Why?

15:43.150 --> 15:44.693
Because of the countryside attitude.

15:44.777 --> 15:46.070
Look it up on the internet.

15:46.153 --> 15:47.947
People even take pills because of it.

15:48.030 --> 15:49.323
That's going too far.

15:49.406 --> 15:50.991
I know, right?

15:51.075 --> 15:53.285
So that's why I looked into it.

15:53.369 --> 15:57.790
They whine over the smallest things,
blaming it on the social dynamic.

15:57.873 --> 16:00.250
When the city folks
meet someone like your wife,

16:00.793 --> 16:03.879
they'll know exactly what they're in for.

16:03.963 --> 16:06.340
They'll say she's the real deal.

16:06.423 --> 16:08.217
Who do you think you are?

16:08.300 --> 16:09.885
Are you trying to start a fight?

16:10.511 --> 16:12.596
This is it. This is a textbook attitude.

16:12.680 --> 16:15.015
I'm about to pee my pants
from just watching you.

16:15.099 --> 16:17.518
Let's take this face right to that lady
and show her.

16:17.601 --> 16:18.435
You brat.

16:18.519 --> 16:20.896
Then she'll pack up immediately
and go back.

16:20.980 --> 16:23.357
-Hey.
-Hey, Seong-man.

16:24.024 --> 16:25.109
We need to eat.

16:25.192 --> 16:28.362
I'm pressuring her
from every direction right now.

16:28.445 --> 16:31.031
The flower of Angok.
The attitude of Angok.

16:31.115 --> 16:34.535
All I'm saying is that you should
go to her and teach her a lesson.

16:34.618 --> 16:36.578
What do you mean "flower"?

16:36.662 --> 16:38.288
Stop the gibberish and get lost.

16:38.372 --> 16:39.456
And you.

16:39.957 --> 16:42.751
If you don't show up with money next time,
you're dead meat.

16:43.293 --> 16:44.211
Listen.

16:45.129 --> 16:48.590
Not me, but you should get the money
ready for the building

16:48.674 --> 16:50.509
I'm leaving. The kimchi looks good.

16:50.592 --> 16:52.678
-Did you just use your hand?
-My bad.

16:52.761 --> 16:55.514
-Damn you.
-Look what mess you made.

16:55.597 --> 16:56.473
I'm leaving.

17:10.237 --> 17:11.697
Oh, no.

17:13.323 --> 17:14.658
What do I do?

17:16.827 --> 17:17.995
Give it to me.

17:18.078 --> 17:20.039
-I'm sorry.
-It's fine.

17:21.790 --> 17:23.167
What's wrong?

17:24.251 --> 17:25.502
I'm so sorry.

17:25.586 --> 17:28.714
You should've been more careful.
It's all soaked.

17:28.797 --> 17:30.716
It's fine. I can dry it.

17:36.305 --> 17:38.432
He's going to try to dry it,

17:38.515 --> 17:40.434
so let's check back on that tomorrow.

17:41.935 --> 17:44.438
If it doesn't dry,
I'll buy a new one for the library.

17:44.521 --> 17:47.274
Please drink the water outside
if possible.

17:47.357 --> 17:48.525
I'm sorry.

17:49.026 --> 17:50.861
First, you sleep here without permission,

17:50.944 --> 17:53.197
and now you damage books.
What a catastrophe.

17:53.280 --> 17:55.866
-I'll clean it up.
-I'll find a rag.

17:55.949 --> 17:56.992
Gosh.

18:07.461 --> 18:09.379
Hey, where are you off to now?

18:09.463 --> 18:10.798
Stop bothering me.

18:10.881 --> 18:11.965
Goodness.

18:12.716 --> 18:14.760
Are you not going to say hello
to your dad?

18:15.803 --> 18:16.845
Whatever.

18:16.929 --> 18:19.098
-That little…
-Come in.

18:19.598 --> 18:21.016
This damn family.

18:21.100 --> 18:23.852
I beg you. Please don't drink too much.

18:23.936 --> 18:25.938
How does he keep that up every day?

18:29.691 --> 18:31.735
Grandma, I'm hungry.

18:32.778 --> 18:35.405
Ha-neul will be here soon.
Do you still want to eat first?

18:38.283 --> 18:39.701
Dried pollack soup again?

18:39.785 --> 18:41.286
I'm sick of it.

18:41.829 --> 18:44.581
Stop making him stuff like that.

18:44.665 --> 18:47.501
If he gets sick enough,
maybe he'll wake up and stop drinking.

18:47.584 --> 18:48.585
Bom.

18:48.669 --> 18:50.712
You shouldn't treat your dad like that.

18:54.133 --> 18:56.677
Hold on. What's wrong with your hand?

18:57.302 --> 18:58.971
I was just bringing your dad home.

18:59.054 --> 19:01.682
I told you to leave him
so he can just die out there.

19:01.765 --> 19:03.684
Goodness, do you hear what you're saying?

19:05.519 --> 19:10.691
That reminds me.
This lady helped me bring your dad home.

19:12.109 --> 19:13.443
Who was it?

19:14.319 --> 19:15.988
I heard she just moved here.

19:18.657 --> 19:21.243
Did she have long hair?

19:21.326 --> 19:24.413
Yes. She had long hair,
and she was pretty.

19:24.496 --> 19:25.956
Grandma!

19:26.039 --> 19:29.084
I told you not to bring
strangers into the house.

19:29.168 --> 19:31.378
-So annoying.
-All right.

19:32.045 --> 19:32.921
NON-POSSESSION

19:33.005 --> 19:34.089
WE'RE SORRY
THIS BOOK IS UNAVAILABLE

19:34.173 --> 19:35.299
It's out of stock.

19:38.719 --> 19:41.555
NON-POSSESSION

19:41.638 --> 19:43.140
It's 65,000 won?

19:43.807 --> 19:47.936
I know they don't make any more copies,
but this is too expensive.

19:48.687 --> 19:51.899
That's my living expenses for a week.

19:55.736 --> 19:57.154
Who are you?

19:58.739 --> 19:59.823
Come here.

20:03.327 --> 20:04.912
Where did you come from?

20:04.995 --> 20:06.830
Why are you alone?

20:08.498 --> 20:10.584
I'm going to get going.

20:13.170 --> 20:14.796
Go on home.

20:18.008 --> 20:19.593
You can't follow me around.

20:19.676 --> 20:21.470
You should stay here.

20:24.598 --> 20:26.892
Stop following me.

20:26.975 --> 20:29.186
Stop! No!

20:30.312 --> 20:32.314
Stop it!

21:00.801 --> 21:01.927
Goodbye.

21:45.220 --> 21:47.973
ANGOK PUBLIC LIBRARY

22:08.368 --> 22:10.370
Hello, you're here again.

22:11.788 --> 22:13.498
Hello, you're here again.

22:14.541 --> 22:16.460
Hello, you're here again.

22:18.962 --> 22:19.880
Hello.

22:20.922 --> 22:22.799
-You're hello again.
-Sorry?

22:22.883 --> 22:24.051
Darn it.

22:24.134 --> 22:26.636
Mr. Librarian. I was wondering…

22:28.055 --> 22:32.059
What happened to the book from yesterday?

22:32.142 --> 22:33.685
Oh, that.

22:46.573 --> 22:47.741
It's frozen.

22:50.494 --> 22:52.120
Why did you put the book in there?

22:54.915 --> 22:59.711
That's because the paper is
made from cellulose.

22:59.795 --> 23:02.422
You see, the covalent bonds of cellulose--

23:02.506 --> 23:04.758
It's supposed to help restore it.

23:04.841 --> 23:06.051
Fascinating, right?

23:06.551 --> 23:07.385
I see.

23:08.929 --> 23:10.514
What a relief.

23:10.597 --> 23:12.182
Thank you so much.

23:12.265 --> 23:14.017
Please be careful next time.

23:14.101 --> 23:16.061
That being said…

23:16.645 --> 23:19.022
-Could I buy you coffee?
-Really?

23:19.815 --> 23:21.608
Great. I wanted to take a break.

23:21.691 --> 23:22.526
Let's go.

23:22.609 --> 23:24.486
I hope you didn't mean
vending machine coffee.

23:24.569 --> 23:25.403
No.

23:31.618 --> 23:32.869
Thank you for the coffee.

23:46.591 --> 23:47.884
You guys can share them.

24:26.089 --> 24:27.549
It's raining.

24:37.100 --> 24:38.101
I almost forgot.

24:49.779 --> 24:51.156
My laundry.

24:56.286 --> 24:57.996
I'm fine.

25:06.755 --> 25:08.006
What the heck?

25:20.727 --> 25:21.811
Use this.

25:25.982 --> 25:27.234
Thank you!

25:28.068 --> 25:30.028
I'll give it back to you tomorrow!

25:46.461 --> 25:48.338
What's going on?

25:48.880 --> 25:49.839
It's nothing.

25:49.923 --> 25:52.175
-Were you in the rain?
-No.

26:16.741 --> 26:17.993
Doggy!

26:21.371 --> 26:22.664
Where are you?

26:24.666 --> 26:26.042
Did you go home?

26:27.711 --> 26:28.670
Doggy!

26:30.005 --> 26:31.172
Oh, my gosh!

26:32.340 --> 26:33.508
What's he doing here?

26:34.884 --> 26:36.094
Where are you?

26:36.594 --> 26:37.804
Doggy.

26:39.848 --> 26:41.266
Why are you there?

26:43.268 --> 26:45.312
Hurry, come on out.

26:51.318 --> 26:52.235
There.

26:54.988 --> 26:56.865
Why are you injured?

26:59.784 --> 27:01.244
Let's go home for now.

27:02.954 --> 27:04.539
Hang in there.

27:14.007 --> 27:17.552
ANGOK SUPERMARKET

27:17.635 --> 27:20.680
VEGETABLES, GOODS, DRINKS

27:22.557 --> 27:24.309
He must be out.

27:26.061 --> 27:28.855
What could I get for you to eat?

27:28.938 --> 27:30.023
Pastry?

27:31.024 --> 27:32.525
Can you eat pastry?

27:33.234 --> 27:35.779
Gosh, you were here.

27:35.862 --> 27:37.655
I was looking for you.

27:37.739 --> 27:40.075
Me? Why?

27:40.658 --> 27:41.868
Well, you know…

27:41.951 --> 27:45.163
Actually, come with me.

27:45.246 --> 27:46.331
Quickly.

27:46.956 --> 27:48.500
Is something wrong?

27:50.960 --> 27:52.337
It's that wall.

27:52.837 --> 27:56.049
You don't need to take it seriously.

27:56.633 --> 27:58.051
I've contacted Mr. Bae,

27:58.134 --> 27:59.928
so he'll be here in a moment.

28:00.011 --> 28:02.680
Go inside for the time being.

28:04.849 --> 28:06.184
No, that's okay.

28:07.060 --> 28:09.813
Mr. Bae has a temper,

28:10.313 --> 28:13.274
so it'd be better if you stay inside
and avoid him.

28:13.358 --> 28:16.653
Go up and act like you're not home.

28:16.736 --> 28:18.279
Don't turn on the lights either.

28:18.947 --> 28:21.991
No, it's fine. I'll stay here.

28:22.742 --> 28:25.578
You have no idea how bad his temper is.

28:25.662 --> 28:28.706
When he sees this,
he'll throw a fit at you.

28:28.790 --> 28:29.749
Just…

28:30.250 --> 28:33.420
Just go inside. You can talk to him later.

28:33.962 --> 28:36.548
It's fine. Head on in.

28:47.934 --> 28:48.977
What the hell?

28:49.728 --> 28:53.148
-Who the hell did this?
-Who made this mess?

28:53.231 --> 28:57.402
Who the hell would do this
to someone else's building?

28:57.485 --> 29:00.780
Dad, keep your voice down.
You don't have to tell the whole town.

29:00.864 --> 29:02.198
What do you mean?

29:02.282 --> 29:03.408
Damn it.

29:04.701 --> 29:07.954
Where did the lady inside go?

29:08.705 --> 29:10.290
I don't think she's home yet.

29:10.373 --> 29:13.501
-The lights are off.
-That girl.

29:13.585 --> 29:16.713
I let her pay only 50,000 won a month
to take care of the building.

29:16.796 --> 29:19.507
But I hear she wanders around town,
drinking every day.

29:19.591 --> 29:22.302
That's why people did this!

29:22.385 --> 29:25.388
Didn't I tell you that we shouldn't
rent out this place to her?

29:25.472 --> 29:27.682
Do you think it makes sense
to live alone here

29:27.766 --> 29:29.601
unless she gave up on her life?

29:29.684 --> 29:32.061
Stop it, guys.

29:32.145 --> 29:34.564
Nothing like this ever happened
when she wasn't here.

29:34.647 --> 29:37.025
As soon as she comes, this happens.

29:38.318 --> 29:39.486
Dad.

29:39.569 --> 29:43.156
Let's give her back the money
and kick her out.

29:43.239 --> 29:45.825
And let's sell the building to Chang-su.

29:45.909 --> 29:46.951
Shut your trap!

29:47.035 --> 29:49.621
Gosh, let's just leave now.

29:50.330 --> 29:53.291
Just what are you good for?
What a useless son.

29:53.374 --> 29:55.668
Erase it immediately
before anyone else sees it.

29:55.752 --> 29:58.296
-Fine, I will. Just go home.
-Let's go.

29:58.379 --> 30:02.634
When this lady comes home,
tell her to behave herself in town.

30:02.717 --> 30:04.302
-Let's go.
-Gosh.

30:04.385 --> 30:06.513
Such a big nuisance came into town.

30:12.268 --> 30:13.436
Gosh, you startled me.

30:14.896 --> 30:16.439
You were inside?

30:17.315 --> 30:19.359
-Give it here. I'll do it.
-No, it's fine.

30:21.319 --> 30:22.612
I'm almost done anyway.

30:29.160 --> 30:30.370
You read the wall, right?

30:31.871 --> 30:34.541
Don't think of staying here long.

30:34.624 --> 30:36.334
It'd be better if you'd leave.

30:37.001 --> 30:39.295
Don't ever talk about what happened today.

30:43.883 --> 30:45.802
I didn't live a nasty life.

30:47.345 --> 30:48.513
What?

30:49.806 --> 30:52.308
I've never caused harm to people here

30:53.184 --> 30:56.020
and I didn't move here
because I've given up on life.

30:57.355 --> 30:58.189
I mean…

30:59.858 --> 31:03.319
I didn't mean that you lived a nasty life.

31:03.403 --> 31:07.115
But you blamed me
for this graffiti on the wall…

31:10.618 --> 31:12.161
What I meant was…

31:13.329 --> 31:15.582
The graffiti wasn't your fault.

31:17.500 --> 31:21.129
I was only saying that a girl
shouldn't be living

31:22.171 --> 31:23.631
in such a run-down place.

31:27.302 --> 31:30.597
Anyway, think again carefully.

31:37.687 --> 31:43.818
ANGOK PUBLIC LIBRARY

31:47.739 --> 31:50.909
TEMPORARILY CLOSED

31:59.417 --> 32:01.169
Don't use your power yet.

32:01.252 --> 32:02.712
There you go.

32:06.090 --> 32:07.216
Hey, Bom.

32:09.135 --> 32:10.428
The library is closed, right?

32:10.511 --> 32:13.598
They both went to Seoul
for Ji-yeong's test.

32:13.681 --> 32:15.099
I never asked.

32:16.643 --> 32:19.103
Seriously? I'm about to feel offended.

32:19.187 --> 32:22.065
I picked out the right person for the job.
You are doing it, right?

32:24.984 --> 32:26.653
I don't want to do it anymore.

32:27.695 --> 32:30.156
Why not? All of a sudden?

32:30.657 --> 32:35.745
Bom, with you making trouble,
Yeo-reum will be running out of here.

32:36.621 --> 32:38.623
Her name is Yeo-reum?

32:39.248 --> 32:42.460
Yes. Lee Yeo-reum? Kim Yeo-reum?
I can't seem to remember.

32:42.543 --> 32:45.296
I don't care.
Anyway, I gave you back the money, okay?

32:45.380 --> 32:47.006
Hey, Bom!

32:48.091 --> 32:49.092
Mr. Bae.

32:49.175 --> 32:52.679
Stop touching your feet
and do some growing up already!

32:52.762 --> 32:54.597
You're so immature.

32:56.516 --> 32:57.809
That little brat.

32:58.476 --> 33:03.064
PUBLIC SERVANT
WRITTEN EXAMINATION CENTER

33:38.933 --> 33:40.226
Did you do well?

33:43.563 --> 33:44.605
I blew it.

33:45.231 --> 33:46.482
I totally blew it.

33:49.444 --> 33:52.155
I had no idea I could blow it this badly.

33:52.905 --> 33:54.824
I'm in disbelief even as I'm saying this.

33:54.907 --> 33:56.951
See? Those people are laughing.

33:57.035 --> 33:59.078
I bet they're laughing
for a different reason.

34:00.621 --> 34:01.789
I'm so damn jealous.

34:02.290 --> 34:03.916
You did your best.

34:04.959 --> 34:06.252
That's what pisses me off.

34:06.335 --> 34:08.713
Why do I always fail
even though I'm trying?

34:13.968 --> 34:15.720
What are you eating by yourself?

34:18.014 --> 34:19.432
I'm so hungry.

34:20.349 --> 34:21.768
Let's go eat.

34:21.851 --> 34:24.270
I've been too nervous
to eat anything since yesterday.

34:24.353 --> 34:25.646
What do you want to eat?

34:27.982 --> 34:30.610
I looked up a restaurant,
and I heard it's really good.

34:30.693 --> 34:32.862
-Shall we go there?
-Sure.

34:39.535 --> 34:41.871
Lady.

34:42.914 --> 34:44.165
Hello.

34:44.665 --> 34:47.126
What do you think you are doing?

34:47.835 --> 34:50.254
Where did you find this dog?

34:51.172 --> 34:53.007
Well…

34:54.383 --> 34:56.302
You're the one who took him, right?

34:57.678 --> 35:00.765
He was shivering in the rain, so…

35:01.766 --> 35:03.309
Do you see the collar or not?

35:03.392 --> 35:06.270
-Sorry?
-The collar.

35:06.896 --> 35:09.065
Do you see it or not?

35:12.777 --> 35:15.196
-Are you his owner?
-Of course, I am.

35:15.738 --> 35:17.448
Then why else would I be here?

35:17.532 --> 35:19.826
How dare you steal someone else's dog?

35:19.909 --> 35:22.245
I didn't steal him.
I just took him in for a night.

35:22.328 --> 35:23.913
It doesn't matter how many nights.

35:23.996 --> 35:25.706
If you took him, it's stealing.

35:26.666 --> 35:28.626
Did you not think about the owner?

35:31.420 --> 35:33.798
I'm sorry for making you worry.

35:33.881 --> 35:35.133
Goodness.

35:35.216 --> 35:38.594
Just look at that getup.

35:39.762 --> 35:40.763
Sorry?

35:40.847 --> 35:42.181
Never mind, what's the point?

35:43.975 --> 35:45.393
Come here.

35:45.476 --> 35:47.353
I said come here.

35:47.436 --> 35:48.563
You brat. You come here.

35:48.646 --> 35:50.064
Are you really the owner?

35:50.148 --> 35:52.650
I am the owner.
Why would I be doing this if I wasn't?

35:52.733 --> 35:54.110
Come here.

35:54.193 --> 35:55.778
-I said come here.
-Don't do that!

35:55.862 --> 35:58.239
You're hurting him!

35:58.322 --> 36:01.159
I'm grabbing my own dog!
What's your problem?

36:01.242 --> 36:02.243
Move!

36:02.326 --> 36:03.703
-Come!
-Stop!

36:03.786 --> 36:05.329
-Come on.
-You're hurting him!

36:05.413 --> 36:08.082
-You shouldn't treat him like that.
-Why do you care?

36:08.166 --> 36:09.792
-Come!
-Stop.

36:09.876 --> 36:11.669
-You come here.
-No.

36:11.752 --> 36:13.337
Stop it.

36:14.005 --> 36:15.923
What do you think you're doing?

36:16.007 --> 36:16.966
Give him to me.

36:17.049 --> 36:19.218
Just sell him to me.

36:19.302 --> 36:20.678
I'll take him home.

36:20.761 --> 36:22.972
What? Sell him to you?

36:23.472 --> 36:24.974
Goodness.

36:25.057 --> 36:25.892
All right, then.

36:26.559 --> 36:28.144
How much will you pay?

36:28.853 --> 36:30.479
How much do you want?

36:32.940 --> 36:34.233
Give me 300,000 won.

36:34.317 --> 36:35.443
What?

36:35.526 --> 36:37.862
What? You don't want to?

36:40.364 --> 36:41.532
Then give him back.

36:41.616 --> 36:43.993
No. I'll give you the money.

36:45.661 --> 36:48.581
Please wait here for a moment.

36:51.083 --> 36:53.002
Leave the dog here.

36:53.085 --> 36:54.795
Do you take me for a fool?

36:59.884 --> 37:01.594
I'll be right back.

37:02.595 --> 37:04.013
Come here.

37:04.096 --> 37:05.598
Where do you think you're going?

37:15.316 --> 37:17.443
Please select the amount
you want to withdraw.

37:17.526 --> 37:20.196
There have been fraud cases…

37:27.203 --> 37:28.955
Are you sure about this place?

37:32.124 --> 37:32.959
Dae-bum.

37:33.542 --> 37:35.336
You know I really like you, right?

37:36.003 --> 37:37.004
Yes.

37:38.839 --> 37:39.882
Let's go.

37:46.639 --> 37:48.599
Hello, I'm Cho Ji-yeong.

37:48.683 --> 37:49.725
Hello.

37:52.561 --> 37:54.480
Hey, Ahn Dae-bum.

37:54.563 --> 37:55.856
It's been a while.

37:55.940 --> 37:57.149
Hey, Dae-bum.

37:57.233 --> 37:58.567
You look great.

38:02.071 --> 38:04.031
You'll have to excuse me, Professor.

38:05.032 --> 38:05.950
Dae-bum.

38:06.450 --> 38:07.827
Dae-bum. Hey.

38:21.299 --> 38:22.675
Here you go, 300,000 won.

38:23.592 --> 38:25.469
I can take him now, right?

38:26.637 --> 38:29.473
Consider yourself lucky
that I'm leaving it at this.

38:29.557 --> 38:32.643
We've lost so much thanks to you
moving into that building.

38:32.727 --> 38:36.188
You should be thanking me for
letting this slide with just 300,000 won.

38:36.856 --> 38:38.232
What are you talking about?

38:39.233 --> 38:41.819
I don't know what you were up to
or where you came from,

38:41.902 --> 38:44.613
but not a soul in this town likes you.

38:44.697 --> 38:46.407
So behave yourself.

38:46.490 --> 38:48.909
-Don't drag our town through the dirt.
-Hey.

38:49.702 --> 38:51.454
Aren't you being too harsh?

38:51.537 --> 38:54.248
I've seen you pay dog traders 10,000 won

38:54.332 --> 38:56.459
for them to take these dogs
off your hands.

38:56.542 --> 38:58.419
How can you take 300,000 won from her?

38:59.253 --> 39:01.130
Why are you butting in?

39:01.213 --> 39:03.632
Whatever. Just give her back the money.

39:04.216 --> 39:06.469
Why do you care?

39:06.552 --> 39:08.971
Why do you care
if I take 300,000 won or 400,000 won?

39:09.055 --> 39:10.681
I don't care.

39:10.765 --> 39:12.975
I'm just worried you might make her think

39:13.059 --> 39:14.935
that everyone in our town is a fraud.

39:15.019 --> 39:17.605
What? A fraud?

39:18.230 --> 39:20.191
My goodness.

39:20.274 --> 39:23.194
You're just like
that drunkard father of yours.

39:23.277 --> 39:26.280
Look how disrespectful
you are to your elders.

39:26.364 --> 39:28.032
What did you just say?

39:28.616 --> 39:31.494
How about I show you
what a drunkard's daughter can do?

39:31.577 --> 39:33.788
You little punk. How dare you?

39:35.873 --> 39:38.167
You can have this money back.

39:38.250 --> 39:40.336
You sold this dog to me.

39:40.419 --> 39:43.089
I'm not selling him. I won't!

39:43.172 --> 39:45.216
-Give him back.
-No.

39:45.299 --> 39:47.676
-Give him back to me!
-You sold him though.

39:47.760 --> 39:49.178
Let me take him!

39:49.261 --> 39:51.514
I'll raise him well.

39:51.597 --> 39:52.723
Really?

39:53.349 --> 39:55.935
Then give me 150,000 won more.

39:57.061 --> 39:58.354
What did you say?

39:58.437 --> 40:02.650
Since she's accusing me of being a fraud,

40:02.733 --> 40:04.318
I want to get paid more.

40:04.402 --> 40:06.362
Hey, just don't buy him.

40:06.445 --> 40:08.823
You can find dogs like these
anywhere in this town.

40:13.869 --> 40:15.538
Please wait here a moment then.

40:16.288 --> 40:17.790
Hey, stop.

40:19.542 --> 40:22.503
Hey, aren't you stepping over the line?

40:22.586 --> 40:24.088
Seriously? 450,000 won?

40:24.171 --> 40:25.798
You stay out of this.

40:25.881 --> 40:27.508
What do you mean, "stay out"?

40:27.591 --> 40:29.343
Are you that desperate for money?

40:29.427 --> 40:31.095
You've got to be out of your mind!

40:31.178 --> 40:35.683
You should learn how to treat your elders
before going to school.

40:35.766 --> 40:36.892
Get lost!

40:38.727 --> 40:40.688
I'll charge her more if you don't go.

40:41.814 --> 40:44.191
Damn you!

40:44.275 --> 40:48.362
That insolent little brat.

40:58.289 --> 41:01.000
Hey, Dae-bum.
I'd rather have you yell at me.

41:01.083 --> 41:04.044
You're driving me nuts.

41:04.128 --> 41:05.921
Professor Lee called me a few days ago

41:06.005 --> 41:08.466
and begged me
to arrange a meeting with you.

41:08.549 --> 41:11.093
To be frank, I don't understand
why you're like this.

41:11.177 --> 41:12.261
What's wrong with you?

41:12.344 --> 41:14.680
People dream of working in those places.

41:15.556 --> 41:18.684
But I'm happy where I am.

41:20.311 --> 41:22.813
What's good about
working part-time at a library?

41:23.397 --> 41:26.650
And you've gotten better too.

41:29.612 --> 41:31.989
All right. Fine. I'm sorry.

41:33.365 --> 41:36.452
If I have to arrange another meeting,
I'll discuss it with you.

41:36.535 --> 41:37.703
But,

41:38.329 --> 41:40.873
don't just refuse.
Give it some serious thought.

41:43.334 --> 41:44.335
Gosh.

41:45.544 --> 41:49.215
I'm just sad because
the Japanese restaurant was wasted.

41:49.298 --> 41:51.175
I heard the food is really good there.

41:57.515 --> 42:00.309
This is the thesis you wrote before.

42:00.392 --> 42:02.019
It's from Professor Lee.

42:02.937 --> 42:04.146
I'll leave it here.

42:04.230 --> 42:06.190
Hey, don't get mad at me.

42:07.733 --> 42:09.235
Don't.

42:33.968 --> 42:35.177
I'm sorry.

42:36.679 --> 42:37.846
To be honest,

42:39.473 --> 42:41.225
I hesitated

42:42.101 --> 42:43.686
when I was withdrawing the money.

42:46.063 --> 42:47.189
I'm sorry.

42:57.616 --> 42:58.659
Hello?

42:59.243 --> 43:00.953
Hey, Yeo-reum. Are you doing okay?

43:01.453 --> 43:03.414
Hey, is something wrong?

43:04.123 --> 43:04.999
Hey.

43:05.082 --> 43:07.710
Can't an older brother call his sister
to check on her?

43:08.252 --> 43:09.878
All right. Just wait.

43:10.754 --> 43:12.548
-Is your wife next to you?
-What?

43:13.257 --> 43:14.300
Yes.

43:14.925 --> 43:17.511
The thing is, Yeo-reum…

43:28.480 --> 43:32.151
You took Mom's house and her money.

43:32.776 --> 43:36.196
That ring is all I have left of Mom.

43:36.780 --> 43:37.906
I know.

43:37.990 --> 43:40.492
But you know Gyu-beom…

43:41.160 --> 43:45.372
All of his friends are
studying abroad every vacation,

43:45.456 --> 43:47.249
but Gyu-beom never went.

43:47.333 --> 43:49.335
Tell her he's going to the Philippines.

43:49.418 --> 43:51.795
I got it.
Can't you see I'm talking to her?

43:54.632 --> 43:56.258
Is this your wife's idea?

43:56.342 --> 43:58.636
Does she want to sell
Mom's ring for the trip?

43:59.261 --> 44:01.221
That's not it. Yeo-reum.

44:01.889 --> 44:05.684
Don't you also feel bad
that your nephew is losing confidence

44:06.310 --> 44:08.979
because he's never been abroad before?

44:09.605 --> 44:10.731
Hey.

44:11.982 --> 44:13.359
Do you even…

44:14.777 --> 44:17.071
know how I'm living right now?

44:17.154 --> 44:18.739
I know.

44:18.822 --> 44:19.948
I do, but…

44:20.658 --> 44:23.160
My family is short on money right now.

44:23.702 --> 44:25.287
Am I not family?

45:41.321 --> 45:45.117
So what on earth is it
that you're talking about?

45:45.200 --> 45:46.785
Tell me.

45:46.869 --> 45:49.663
Physics is an area of study.

45:49.746 --> 45:51.832
The fact that it's named "entropy"

45:51.915 --> 45:55.043
doesn't mean it has
the same physical quantity.

45:55.836 --> 45:56.712
What the…

45:58.130 --> 45:59.465
I did it correctly.

46:00.007 --> 46:01.675
I solved it correctly.

46:02.801 --> 46:04.261
I solved it correctly.

46:59.983 --> 47:02.569
Why do you show up in front of me 

47:02.653 --> 47:05.072
Whenever I'm drunk…

47:05.155 --> 47:07.199
Gosh, your money. Hey!

47:07.282 --> 47:08.784
The liquor drank you last night.

47:08.867 --> 47:09.826
Zero?

47:09.910 --> 47:11.036
She lost all her money?

47:11.119 --> 47:13.872
Someone must have taken it.
It's money in a plastic bag.

47:13.956 --> 47:15.082
Damn it!

47:15.958 --> 47:17.167
That long-haired guy is Dae-bum.

47:17.251 --> 47:19.795
I should have taken you
back to your home safely.

47:19.878 --> 47:21.088
Who is it?

47:21.630 --> 47:24.007
Did you just not care
since it's not your problem?

47:24.091 --> 47:25.050
I'm sorry.

47:25.133 --> 47:27.261
The way I see it,
she'll never find that money.

47:27.803 --> 47:30.931
Subtitle translation by: Jea-Heon Chung
